It was the very first event of the Conservative Political Action Conference in February, and Candace Owens could hardly believe she was speaking.
We are watching the slow, and painful, death of the mainstream media.
It has since spawned dozens more under her channel, Red Pill Black, a nod to The Matrix and her purported political awakening.
As conservatives have gone from railing against the mainstream media to abandoning it altogether, they’ll tune in to new platforms and new people like Owens.
We are watching the slow, and painful, death of the mainstream media,” she said at CPAC, joining a co-panelist to “wave goodbye” to the media gathered in the back.